===Etymology===
Originally verb sense “drink heartily”, from {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|bibben|lang=enm}}, either from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term/t|la|bibō||I drink}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*peh₃-}}, or of imitative origin. Noun sense (clothing) presumably either because worn while drinking, or because the clothing itself “drinks up” spills.<ref>{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}</ref>

